Cheltenham Town defender Ibrahim Bakare's story so far
arts.sum: Bakare played two trial games in a week for Cardiff, who were managed by Mick McCarthy and he signed for the Championship club in March 2021. During his school days, along with singing in the choir and playing a range of sports including netball, Bakare enjoyed being part of the debate team, which he believes has stood him in good stead for handling the often intimidating football environment.

arts.ttl: Defender's best performance yet, Arkell Jude-Boyd's unbelievable goal and striving for more - Cheltenham Town boss Michael Flynn after Morecambe win
arts.sum: Competition has been good at the minute and we have got goals in us as well - it's been pleasing, but there is lots to improve on. We were making the subs, just before his goal and I am pleased for him because he does work his socks off and he's an important cog in the team.
